row our team and facilities,\\u201d said Dr. Reza Chaji, CEO of VueReal. \\nVueReal, a player in the automotive industry, is expanding into the consumer market, targeting wearable devices, TVs, IT applications, and augmented reality products.\\nThe expanded manufacturing space includes a new production line to scale up solutions for established display manufacturers and smaller companies. This line will serve as a blueprint for partners to integrate into their facilities.\\n\\n\\nCategories News Tags MicroLED, VueReal \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nPlease enable JavaScript in your browser to complete this form.Multiple Choice *\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nComment\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCollaborate\\nEmail *Name *Comment or Message *Submit \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nRelated Posts\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMicroLED TVs Going Nowhere\\n\\n\\nOmid Rahmat\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nVueReal Announces Major Expansion and New Production Line\\n\\n\\nShawnee Blackwood\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMiniLED Magic: Outshining OLED and MicroLED for Sunlight Readability\\n\\n\\nJoseph Bryans\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMicroLED\\u2019s Future: Perspectives From Display Week 2024\\n\\n\\nSweta Dash\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nJon Peddie Research4 St. Gabrielle Ct.Tiburon, California 94920\\n415-435-9368\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\u00a9 2024 Jon Peddie Research\\n\\n\\nAbout us | Privacy Policy | terms of service | contact\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n        \"type\": \"Document\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"lc\": 1,\n      \"type\": \"constructor\",\n      \"id\": [\n        \"langchain\",\n        \"schema\",\n        \"document\",\n        \"Document\"\n      ],\n      \"kwargs\": {\n        \"metadata\": {\n          \"source\": \"https://www.theglobeandmail.com/investing/markets/markets-news/GetNews/27431899/neareye-display-market-size-projected-to-reach-usd-53-billion-by-2027-at-a-cagr-of-247\",\n          \"title\": \"The Globe and Mail - The Globe and Mail\",\n          \"description\": \"GetNews Press Release.\",\n          \"language\": \"en-CA\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"The Globe and Mail - The Globe and Mail\\n\\nSkip to main contentSearchNewslettersWatchlistHomeWatchlistFor YouCanadaWorldBusinessInvestingPersonal FinanceOpinionPoliticsSportsLifeArtsDriveReal EstateLatest in Flash Sale$0.99/weekDigital accessDigital + home deliveryNear-Eye Display Market Size Projected to Reach USD 5.3 Billion by 2027, at a CAGR of 24.7%GetNews - TGAM - GetNews - Tue Jul 16, 5:06PM CDT \\\"Near-Eye Display Market Size\\\"  The Global Near-Eye Display Market Size is projected to reach USD 5.3 billion by 2027, growing at a CAGR of 24.7% during the forecast period. The global Near-Eye Display (NED) Market is anticipated to achieve remarkable growth, with its market size projected to reach USD 5.3 billion by 2027, exhibiting a robust Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 24.7% during the forecast period from 2022 to 2027. This growth is driven by a surge in demand across various applications, particularly in augmented reality (AR) and virtual reality (VR) sectors, healthcare, automotive, and consumer electronics.Download PDF Brochure @ https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/pdfdownloadNew.asp?id=204073371Key SegmentsTechnology:OLED: Expected to dominate due to its superior display quality and energy efficiency.LCD: Continues to hold a significant share owing to its cost-effectiveness.Micro-LED: Emerging as a strong contender with benefits such as higher brightness and longer lifespan.\\u00a0Device Type:AR Devices: Increasingly used in industrial applications and gaming.VR Devices: Gaining traction in entertainment and simulation training.\\u00a0End-Use Industry:Consumer Electronics: Major driver with continuous advancements in AR/VR headsets and smart glasses.Healthcare: Rising adoption in surgical procedures and training.Automotive: Integration in head-up displays (HUDs) for advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS).\\u00a0Inquire Before Buying @ https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/Enquiry_Before_BuyingNew.asp?id=204073371Growth DriversRising Demand for AR and VR: The booming AR and VR industries are significant growth drivers, with applications ranging from gaming and entertainment to training and education.Technological Advancements: Continuous innovation in display technologies, including the development of OLED, Micro-LED, and holographic displays, is propelling market growth.Increased Investment in R&D: Significant investments by key players in research and development are leading to the introduction of advanced NED products.ChallengesHigh Costs: The high initial cost of near-eye display devices poses a significant challenge, limiting their adoption, particularly in developing regions.Technical Limitations: Issues such as latency, resolution, and the bulkiness of devices can hinder market growth.Regulatory Hurdles: Navigating through regulatory standards and obtaining necessary approvals can be time-consuming and costly.View detailed Table of Content here - https://www.marketsandmarkets.com/Market-Reports/near-eye-display-market-204073371.htmlOpportunitiesHealthcare Sector: There is a growing opportunity in the healthcare sector for applications in surgery, diagnostics, and patient care.Automotive Industry: The integration of NEDs in automotive HUDs offers substantial growth potential, especially with the rise of autonomous and connected vehicles.Consumer Market Expansion: The expanding consumer electronics market, with a focus on smart glasses and advanced gaming solutions, presents lucrative opportunities.Key PlayersSony CorporationSamsung ElectronicsMicrosoft CorporationKopin CorporationHimax TechnologieseMagin CorporationMedia ContactCompany Name:MarketsandMarkets\\u2122 Research Private Ltd.Contact Person: Mr. Aashish MehraEmail:Send EmailPhone: 18886006441Address:630 Dundee Road Suite 430City: NorthbrookState: IL 60062Country: