\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n   \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nNews Categories\\nHomeRecommended App DevelopersMarkets NewsComputer SupportAsia Pacific NewsMobile Apps NewsMobile ReviewsContact Us\\nSign\\u00a0up\\u00a0for\\u00a0FREE\\nLOGIN\\nHomeBusiness DirectoryMarkets News \\n\\nTech \\n \\n\\n\\n\\nMarkets Research \\n \\n\\n\\n\\nInformation & Communications Technology \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGuest Post By \\nInsightace Analytic \\n\\nInformation Technology Markets\\n\\n\\n\\n\\t\\t2024-07-17\\t\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tVirtual Reality Exposure Therapy Market Stepping into Recovery: The Burgeoning Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy Market As Revealed In New Report\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGuest Post By \\nInsightace Analytic \\n\\nInformation Technology Markets\\n\\n\\n\\n\\t\\t2024-07-17\\t\\n\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tInsightAce Analytic\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGuest Post By \\nInsightace Analytic \\n\\nInformation Technology Markets\\n\\n\\n\\n\\t\\t2024-07-17\\t\\n\\n\\n\\nVirtual Reality Exposure Therapy Market to Record an Exponential CAGR by 2030 - Exclusive Report by InsightAce Analytic\\nInsightAce Analytic Pvt. Ltd. announces the release of a market assessment report on the \\\"Global Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy Market- by Components (Virtual Reality Headset, Virtual Reality Earphones, Virtual Reality Software & Modules, Virtual Reality Workstation, Virtual Reality Position Tracker/ Sensors, Biofeedback Monitor and Other Components), Application (Mental Disorder & Addiction Management, Stroke Management, Pediatric Management, Education & Medical Training and Other Application), End User (Hospitals, Therapy Clinics, & Surgical Centers, Research & Training Organizations and Other End Users), Trends, Industry Competition Analysis, Revenue and Forecast To 2030.\\\"\\nGet a free sample copy of the report: www.insightaceanalytic.com/request-sample/1306\\nAccording to the latest research by InsightAce Analytic, the global Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy market is expected to show a CAGR of 33.90% during a forecast period of 2024-2031.\\nVirtual Reality Exposure Therapy: A More Immersive Approach\\nVirtual reality exposure therapy (VRET) is a sophisticated and immersive form of therapy that utilizes computer-generated simulations to expose patients to feared or anxiety-provoking situations in a safe, controlled environment. This therapist-assisted treatment leverages human-computer interaction through a head-mounted display with video screens, headphones, and a head-tracking device. This combination allows patients to actively engage in a three-dimensional computer environment.\\nHow VRET Works\\nThe hardware and software components of VRET work together to create a virtual environment where patients can see and interact with objects and scenarios relevant to their specific therapy needs. This immersive setting allows them to confront their fears in a safe and controlled way. For example, a patient with a fear of heights could be virtually exposed to progressively higher situations, such as climbing a ladder or standing on a balcony.\\nMarket Growth Drivers\\nThe VRET market is expected to experience significant growth driven by several key factors:\\n\\nRising Prevalence of Anxiety Disorders: The increasing rates of heart surgery, stroke, and mental health issues, such as anxiety disorders, are creating a greater demand for effective treatment solutions. VRET offers a promising approach for managing these conditions.\\nGovernment Support for Digital Healthcare: Government initiatives promoting the use of internet-of-things (IoT) and artificial intelligence (AI) in healthcare applications are creating a favorable environment for the adoption of VRET.\\nPopularity of AR/VR Technology: The growing popularity of augmented reality (AR) and VR products, particularly in developed nations, is driving interest in VRET as a therapeutic tool.\\n\\nAdvantages Over Traditional Therapy\\nVRET offers several advantages over traditional therapy approaches:\\n\\nCost-Effectiveness: VRET can be more cost-effective than traditional methods, as it eliminates the need for exposure to real-world situations that may be expensive or impractical.\\nImproved Data Collection: VRET allows for the collection of more accurate and valuable data on patient responses compared to traditional methods. This data can then be used to refine treatment approaches and potentially guide the development of medication-based therapies.\\n\\nMarket Challenges\\nDespite its potential, the VRET market also faces some challenges:\\n\\nLimited Accessibility: The high costs associated with VRET technology can limit accessibility, particularly in developing countries.\\nLack of Awareness: A lack of awareness about VRET as a treatment option, especially in developing regions, can hinder market growth.\\nCompetition: The increasing competition among major players in the VRET market can put pressure on pricing and innovation.\\n\\nLooking Ahead\\nBy addressing these challenges and leveraging its unique advantages, VRET has the potential to become a mainstream therapeutic tool, offering a more immersive and effective approach to treating anxiety disorders and phobias.\\nNorth America is anticipated to be the major contributor to the Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy market over the forecast years, with most of its revenue coming from Canada and the US. Patient and medical staff awareness of virtual reality exposure therapy's benefits for treating mental illness and other diseases is the critical element fueling this market's dominance. One of the main factors fueling market expansion in this sector is the increasing government expenditure on healthcare infrastructure. Much money is being spent in the region to combine cutting-edge medical procedures with immersive technology, likely to hasten market expansion there. Similar to this, expanding regional markets would be encouraged by increased healthcare R&D.\\nIn addition, the Asia Pacific Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy market is expected to grow significantly during the forecast period. Growth in virtual reality exposure therapy use in this market is expected due to increased stroke cases in nations like Japan, Taiwan, China, and India. Additionally, the fact that most workstation and electronic parts suppliers have their headquarters in Asia-Pacific would promote the adoption and understanding of such treatment.\\nMajor market players operating in the Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy market include\\nFirsthand Technology, Atheer, Medical Realities, Oculus VR, Echopixel, Osso VR, Surgical Theatre, Augmedic, and Truevision, among others. (Other companies include: Vicarious Surgical, Health Scholars, Oxford VR, Limbix, KineQuantum, Google, Proprio, Pious, Microsoft, Mindmaze, Samsung Electronics, ImmersiveTouch, Virtually Better, Accelerated Care Plus Corporation, Emotions, Vivid Vision, Karuna Labs, Fundamentalvar, Sentier, Augmented Intelligence, Reducept, Neuro Rehab VR, JOGO Health, Oncomfort, Virtualis, Six VR, FeelsGood, and Meta Medical VR).\\nRecent collaborations and agreements in the market:\\n\\nIn August 2020, The US company ImmersiveTouch, which offers a VR rehabilitation program for mental health, won a UK Digital Experience Award, and Oxford VR's (UK) mental health program took home the Gold Award for Best Use of Emerging Technology.\\nIn April 2020, Released April 2020, Oxford VR's (UK) automated virtual reality therapy was also featured in the NHSX Global Digital Exemplar. (GDE). The company's concept has been accepted and integrated into the NHS's Improving Access to Psychological Therapies (IAPT) services, which provide mental health care.\\n\\nCurious about this latest version of the report? Obtain Report Details @ www.insightaceanalytic.com/enquiry\\u2026uying/1306\\nMarket Segments\\nGlobal Virtual Reality Exposure Therapy Market, by Componen