t-car-museum/\",\n          \"title\": \"Green light for Palmer to build biggest car museum\",\n          \"language\": \"en-AU\"\n        },\n        \"page_content\": \"\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGreen light for Palmer to build biggest car museum\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\n\\nLetters\\n\\n\\nLifestyle\\nProperty\\nLearning\\nCouncil\\nBusiness\\nCommunity\\n\\nGallery\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSearch\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News \\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nHome\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n100% Locally Owned, Independent and Free \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\n\\nLetters\\n\\n\\nLifestyle\\nProperty\\nLearning\\nCouncil\\nBusiness\\nCommunity\\n\\nGallery\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nSearch \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nHome\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n100% Locally Owned, Independent and Free \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHome\\nNews\\n\\nSport\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\n\\nLetters\\n\\n\\nLifestyle\\nProperty\\nLearning\\nCouncil\\nBusiness\\nCommunity\\n\\nGallery\\n\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nSearch \\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\nHome\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHomeNews\\n\\nMining magnate receives approval to build Australia's biggest car museum\\u00a0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nClive Palmer has approval for his latest unexpected venture. Picture: Shutterstock.\\n\\n\\n\\nBy AAP\\n\\n12 July 2024 \\n\\nNews\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nDo you have a news tip? Click here to send to our news team.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nNews\\nProminent bridge\\u2019s lifespan extended by 50 years\\nA well-known bridge in the middle of a tourist hub has received a $3.5 million renovation.\\n\\nThe Garth Prowd Bridge on Noosa Parade is now More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  18 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nNews\\nPipeline completed as water supply project progresses\\nA 2.6km pipeline has been installed to deliver more water to a community that is expected to be home to more than 21,000 people.\\n\\nA More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  18 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nLocal\\nCoast man facing multiple charges following crash\\nPolice have charged a 40-year-old Birtinya man following a single-vehicle traffic crash on the Gold Coast last night.\\n\\nAbout 11.34pm, police were called to reports More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  18 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nOpinion\\nAshley Robinson: actions used to have consequences\\nDiscipline is on everyone\\u2019s lips at the moment, with a youth crime wave seemingly out of control.\\n\\nThere are two sides to the argument \\u2013 More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nAshley Robinson -  18 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nCommunity\\nBig-name entertainers on program for arts festival\\nA Gold Logie-winning TV host and comedian is among the headliners for one of the region\\u2019s most anticipated arts and cultural festivals, which swings More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nSunshine Coast News -  17 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\nLocal\\nCourt approval means town can have its first supermarket\\n4A proposed shopping centre for a Coast town has the go-ahead after the council and an applicant reached agreement during a court appeal.\\n\\nEumundi Holdings More\\n\\nMore\\n\\n\\n\\nJanine Hill -  17 July 2024 0 \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nThere\\u2019s been Titanic II, even an A-League club.\\nAnd who can forget Jeff, the ill-fated animatronic Tyrannosaurus rex?\\nNow colourful billionaire Clive Palmer has approval for his latest unexpected venture \\u2013 Australia\\u2019s biggest car museum.\\nJust weeks after it appeared to stall, Mr Palmer\\u2019s display of vintage vehicles worth more than $200 million is now set to be on show at a property west of Brisbane.\\nThe mining magnate pulled the pin on a planning application to build the ambitious project at his Palmer Coolum Resort on the Sunshine Coast in June after locals claimed it would be an \\u201ceyesore\\u201d.\\nInstead, he set his sights on a property near Lowood, a 90-minute drive from Brisbane.\\nThe local Somerset Council on Wednesday officially approved the project that will feature more than 1000 cars and 300 motorcycles.\\n\\u201cWe are hoping it provides a tourism boost for the region,\\u201d Somerset Mayor Jason Wendt told AAP.\\nMr Palmer is no stranger to bold ideas.\\nThe former politician was the owner of A-League club Gold Coast United for three seasons from 2009 before its licence was revoked following his running battle with the governing body.\\nAn artist\\u2019s impression of the proposed car museum at Palmer Coolum Resort, a plan that was ultimately scrapped.\\nHe also dabbled in tourism, scattering more than 150 replica dinosaurs next to his Coolum resort in a theme park dubbed \\u201cPalmersaurus\\u201d.\\nHailed as the \\u201cworld\\u2019s largest dinosaur park\\u201d, its drawcard was Jeff, a 10m animatronic T-rex that had a fiery extinction in 2015 when it burnt down due to an electrical fault.\\nThen there\\u2019s Titanic II.\\nThe one-time senator in March announced it was full steam ahead \\u2013 again \\u2013 for his plan to build the Titanic replica and recreate the doomed cruise, 11 years after first floating the idea.\\nMr Palmer is now all revved up to build the country\\u2019s biggest car museum following the council\\u2019s development application approval.\\nDo you have an opinion to share? Submit a Letter to the Editor at Sunshine Coast News via news@sunshinecoastnews.com.au.\\u00a0You must include your name and suburb.\\nThe Lowood site will feature 11 buildings for vehicle display along with 10 accommodation units, a cafe and a gift shop.\\nThe museum\\u2019s gross floor area is 43,000sq m, about the size of four NRL fields.\\nIt is set to eclipse South Australia\\u2019s National Motor Museum as the nation\\u2019s biggest car display.\\nThe project is expected to create about 80 jobs during construction \\u2013 which is set to start in 2025 \\u2013 and employ about 30 full-time staff.\\n\\u201cWe are excited about the opportunities this poses for the region,\\u201d Mr Wendt said.\\nHelp keep independent and fair Sunshine Coast news coming by subscribing to our FREE daily news feed. All it requires is your name and email at the bottom of this article.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSubscribe to SCN\\u2019s Daily News\\n\\n\\nHiddenFirst Name(Required) Email(Required)\\n\\nNameThis field is for validation purposes and should be left unchanged.\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nGo backReturn Home\\n\\n\\n[scn_go_back_button]\\nReturn Home\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nShare\\nFacebookLinkedinWhatsAppEmailCopy URL\\n\\n\\nShare\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\n \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nOur Sister Publications\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nAdd to Device\\nSubscribe\\nAdvertise\\nAbout SCN\\nContact Us\\nSubmit Story Ideas\\nEditorial Policy\\nTerms of Use\\nPrivacy Policy\\nAdvertising T & C\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nAdd to Device\\nSubscribe\\nAdvertise\\nAbout SCN\\nContact Us\\nSubmit Story Ideas\\nEditorial Policy\\nTerms of Use\\nPrivacy Policy\\nAdvertising T & C\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFollow Us\\n\\n\\nFacebookInstagramLinkedinYoutube\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCopyright \\u00a9 Sunshine Coast News 2023\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\